00:21.100 --> 00:22.039
You need another bag ?

00:22.766 --> 00:23.798
Yo, Mike, where you at ?

00:24.443 --> 00:25.147
Yeah, over here.

00:26.225 --> 00:26.874
Drug war ?

00:31.611 --> 00:33.758
Barksdals coming back
on my boy Marlo, hmm ?

00:35.823 --> 00:36.315
Shit.

00:37.441 --> 00:37.816
Got it.

00:46.155 --> 00:47.622
Yo man, I don't know where we at.

00:48.654 --> 00:50.612
We are in Baltimore, Lamar.

00:51.598 --> 00:52.701
Baltimore, Maryland.

02:00.960 --> 02:03.846
That's the second crib of mine
them motherfuckers cracked this week.

02:04.621 --> 02:06.005
Stir up a hornet's nest

02:06.720 --> 02:08.186
no tellin' who gonna get stung.

02:17.832 --> 02:19.275
All paranoid an' shit.

02:20.312 --> 02:20.839
Got to be.

02:38.171 --> 02:39.181
They got Latroy.

02:42.556 --> 02:44.609
What the fuck is y'all
on the streets for, man ?

02:44.633 --> 02:47.025
Don't you all know there's
a fucking war going on, man ?

02:47.050 --> 02:48.421
Get the fuck in the truck, man.

03:21.035 --> 03:22.455
What happened to all them towers ?

03:23.581 --> 03:24.543
Slow train comin'.

03:28.977 --> 03:30.044
Reform, Lamar.

03:31.487 --> 03:32.201
Reform.

05:06.944 --> 05:08.069
Reformation

05:28.149 --> 05:30.518
We should be up on
this shit, hearin' voices.

05:30.953 --> 05:33.264
We get a signature number
on Bodie's phone, we will be.

05:33.311 --> 05:35.118
We got enough P.C.
off the burners alone.

05:35.727 --> 05:38.084
Every time these fucking pen
registers click out a call

05:38.119 --> 05:39.371
it screams drug conspiracy.

05:39.395 --> 05:41.272
I'm not the one
takin' the case to court.

05:41.307 --> 05:44.121
Pearlman wants a specific link
to a known drug trafficker.

05:51.185 --> 05:52.194
These drug crews ?

05:52.370 --> 05:54.599
They're dumping phones
every couple weeks at best.

05:54.763 --> 05:57.132
So when we do get a wire up,
it's gonna be a limited run.

05:57.308 --> 05:59.885
And dumping phones doesn't
meet the cellular company's

05:59.897 --> 06:01.928
definition of exigent
circumstance, huh ?

06:03.309 --> 06:04.741
What's your boss willing to do ?

06:05.258 --> 06:05.797
Demper ?

06:06.302 --> 06:09.056
He's a bit too focused on next
year's re-election fight.

06:09.220 --> 06:10.082
How about the feds ?

06:10.486 --> 06:12.282
They say they can't
do anything for us

06:12.563 --> 06:15.155
and if you look at how they use
the federal communications act

06:15.168 --> 06:15.988
they're not lying.

06:16.388 --> 06:18.674
For national security stuff,
they use the Patriot Act

06:18.909 --> 06:20.246
every thing else gets shorted.

06:20.914 --> 06:23.248
The fact is, the industry
has all of us by the balls.

06:26.556 --> 06:27.894
Pardon my french, Your Honor.

06:29.876 --> 06:31.061
Alright, I'll tell you what.

06:31.296 --> 06:32.632
Best I can do for you is this:

06:33.078 --> 06:36.468
You give me a boilerplate affidavit
with the P.C. from the court report

06:37.747 --> 06:40.187
and then as you get fresh
numbers for new disposables

06:40.205 --> 06:40.921
you call me...

06:41.965 --> 06:45.073
anytime, day or night,
to jump phones.

06:45.461 --> 06:46.351
That helps.

06:46.810 --> 06:48.263
But we're still gonna be getting up

06:48.276 --> 06:50.164
on their phones even
as they're coming down.

06:50.172 --> 06:50.946
Yeah, probably so.

06:50.947 --> 06:53.058
- This is so totally...
- fucked up ?

06:55.334 --> 07:02.689
"Je parle français bien,
et tu es très charmant aujourd'hui."

07:08.084 --> 07:09.890
Judge Phelan has you on his mind.

07:10.949 --> 07:12.381
How long has that been going on ?

07:13.166 --> 07:13.893
Started with...

07:15.160 --> 07:17.107
my first jury trial
in his court, I think.

07:17.588 --> 07:18.925
I bet you won all your motions.

07:24.784 --> 07:25.922
You wanted to see me, sir ?

07:26.509 --> 07:27.130
Have a seat.

07:31.846 --> 07:33.727
I wanna thank you for
the loyalty you showed

07:34.514 --> 07:35.382
moving that body.

07:37.175 --> 07:39.181
It wasn't the most
sensible thing, but...

07:39.452 --> 07:40.633
I appreciate it nonetheless.

07:42.056 --> 07:43.278
You're a good man, Sergeant

07:44.189 --> 07:45.268
you got good instincts

07:45.784 --> 07:48.282
and as far as I can tell
you're a decent supervisor.

07:50.053 --> 07:51.027
But from where I sit

07:52.657 --> 07:54.431
you ain't shit when
it come to policin'.

07:55.416 --> 07:57.528
Don't take it personal,
ain't just you.

07:57.551 --> 07:59.452
It's all our young police.

08:00.191 --> 08:01.411
A whole generation of y'all.

08:02.443 --> 08:03.545
Now, you think about it:

08:05.035 --> 08:07.428
You been here over
a year now, Carver.

08:07.464 --> 08:09.399
You got nobody looking out for you

08:09.469 --> 08:11.040
nobody willing to talk to you.

08:12.566 --> 08:13.563
That about sum it up ?

08:15.252 --> 08:16.212
And that's a problem.

08:17.304 --> 08:18.816
And I didn't think
there was anyway

08:18.827 --> 08:20.505
I was ever gonna
get my head around it.

08:20.518 --> 08:22.617
But then Dozerman
gets shot for some bullshit...

08:25.042 --> 08:26.720
and that's when
I 'bout reach my limit.

08:28.044 --> 08:29.840
And that's when the idea
of the free zone

08:29.863 --> 08:30.966
of Hamsterdam come to me.

08:30.989 --> 08:34.049
Because this drug thing,
this ain't police work.

08:34.696 --> 08:35.868
No, it ain't.

08:37.253 --> 08:40.114
I mean, I can send any fool
with a badge and a gun

08:40.126 --> 08:42.554
up on those corners and
jack a crew and grab vials.

08:43.610 --> 08:44.325
But policing ?

08:46.860 --> 08:49.381
You call something a war,
and pretty soon

08:49.382 --> 08:51.897
everybody gonna running
around acting like warriors.

08:53.094 --> 08:55.393
They gonna be runnin'
around on a damn crusade

08:55.402 --> 08:58.181
stormin' corners, slappin' on
cuffs, rackin' up body counts.

08:59.942 --> 09:02.228
And when you at war,
you need a fuckin' enemy.

09:03.156 --> 09:04.187
And pretty soon

09:04.458 --> 09:07.521
damn near everybody on every
corner is your fuckin' enemy

09:08.412 --> 09:11.069
and soon the neighborhood that
you're supposed to be policin'

09:11.367 --> 09:12.752
that's just occupied territory.

09:15.238 --> 09:16.154
You follow this ?

09:17.128 --> 09:17.785
I think so.

09:18.481 --> 09:20.744
Look, the point I'm makin',
Carver, is this...

09:21.226 --> 09:23.818
soldierin' and policin',
they ain't the same thing.

09:24.486 --> 09:26.503
And before we went
and took the wrong turn

09:26.504 --> 09:28.404
and started with these war games

09:29.396 --> 09:32.117
the cop walked a beat,
and he learned that post.

09:34.006 --> 09:36.317
And if there were things
that happened up on that post

09:36.327 --> 09:38.545
whether there be a rape,
a robbery, a shooting...

09:39.378 --> 09:41.947
he had people out there helping
him, feeding him information.

09:43.474 --> 09:46.452
But every time I come to you,
my D.E.U. sergeant

09:46.985 --> 09:47.977
for information

09:48.545 --> 09:50.839
to find out what's going
on out there on them streets

09:52.233 --> 09:53.853
all that came back
was some bullshit.

09:55.674 --> 09:58.476
You had your stats, you had
your arrests, you had your seizures.

09:59.009 --> 10:01.620
But don't none of that amount
to shit when you talking about

10:01.632 --> 10:03.772
protecting a neighborhood
now, do it ?

10:10.978 --> 10:12.515
You know the worst
thing about this

10:13.969 --> 10:15.140
so called drug war ?

10:15.837 --> 10:16.700
To my mind ?

10:20.867 --> 10:23.268
It just ruined this job.

10:26.117 --> 10:26.768
Major ?

10:27.109 --> 10:27.879
What do you got ?

10:28.056 --> 10:28.708
Incoming.

10:29.475 --> 10:30.550
"Sunpapers" reporter.

10:30.929 --> 10:32.680
Been to the free zones,
all three of 'em.

10:35.435 --> 10:36.013
It's begun.

10:41.068 --> 10:43.419
I was thinkin', maybe
we rewrite the affidavit

10:43.431 --> 10:45.879
add some of the stuff we're
gettin' from the pen registers

10:45.890 --> 10:47.841
build the case that way,
take it to the judge.

10:47.865 --> 10:48.881
You have a law degree ?

10:48.989 --> 10:50.915
If you did, it would
be your call to make.

10:51.081 --> 10:53.102
Who would pretend to be
a lawyer that wasn't ?

10:54.403 --> 10:55.089
I'm just saying.

10:55.100 --> 10:56.886
I think we're being
too cautious on this.

10:56.898 --> 10:58.576
We're going the
extra mile for Phelan.

10:58.600 --> 11:01.035
A short cut now could cost us
later in motions hearings.

11:01.165 --> 11:02.768
We drew Phelan on this wiretap ?

11:02.993 --> 11:05.239
That two-faced hack sold
me out the last go-round.

11:05.334 --> 11:05.912
Relax...

11:06.610 --> 11:08.821
he's not running for
a new term. He'll be fine.

11:08.822 --> 11:10.003
He's a piece of shit.

11:10.087 --> 11:12.232
We're all pieces of shit
when we're in your way.

11:12.929 --> 11:14.394
That goes with the territory.

11:25.269 --> 11:26.119
Point taken.

11:28.365 --> 11:30.611
So it's these warehouses

11:30.824 --> 11:34.093
the old Winchester homes and the
dead blocks down by Vincent Street.

11:34.365 --> 11:35.133
All three.

11:36.174 --> 11:38.399
And they're just supposed
to let it go on like this ?

11:38.408 --> 11:41.139
Colvin told us to push the
street dealing in these areas

11:41.222 --> 11:43.225
then we would start
locking people up.

11:43.532 --> 11:45.329
But so far, not a single
fucking arrest.

11:45.683 --> 11:47.114
And they know about this downtown ?

11:47.137 --> 11:49.182
I don't think they have
a fucking clue about it.

11:49.195 --> 11:51.406
But I'd love to be there
when you pop the question.

11:54.161 --> 11:55.131
This is just...

11:56.195 --> 11:57.129
Tell me about it.

12:05.999 --> 12:07.607
Got the place lookin' good.

12:07.725 --> 12:08.292
Yeah.

12:08.493 --> 12:11.627
Now all needs doin' is to go
out and get you some kids.

12:11.910 --> 12:12.721
Come on, man.

12:13.444 --> 12:14.625
You makin' it sound easy

12:15.464 --> 12:16.989
but to tell you the truth

12:17.852 --> 12:20.323
I ain't got no idea how
to go at these hoppers.

12:20.347 --> 12:22.286
I wouldn't lose
any sleep over that.

12:22.924 --> 12:24.404
Nobody else does neither.

12:33.069 --> 12:33.933
We got one.

12:35.153 --> 12:35.875
His grandmother...

12:36.170 --> 12:36.903
<i>Looking for me ?</i>

12:36.915 --> 12:39.775
<i>Look, boy, there's no reason
to leave your clothes in the washer.</i>

12:39.835 --> 12:41.962
<i>How many damn times
do I have to tell you...</i>

12:41.987 --> 12:44.553
<i>Gag, grandma, sorry,
I just forgot, okay ?</i>

12:44.931 --> 12:47.238
<i>But I did pick up the laundry
soap, I picked it up...</i>

12:47.262 --> 12:48.893
Laundry soap,
that's definitely code.

12:48.977 --> 12:51.589
Now, let's listen to an intercept
we made of Bodie Broadus

12:51.590 --> 12:54.130
when we were up on the pay
phones a couple years back.

12:55.264 --> 12:56.141
<i>I'm tellin' ya all</i>

12:56.257 --> 12:58.539
<i>I saw the boy he sayin'
he ain't got that thing.</i>

12:58.763 --> 13:00.206
Same voice, no question.

13:00.454 --> 13:01.494
I'll let the judge know.

13:02.062 --> 13:04.285
Reference the voice comparison
in the court report.

13:04.355 --> 13:05.538
We're up.

13:13.169 --> 13:14.528
Major Colvin, Western district.

13:14.753 --> 13:16.623
Banisky, "Sunpapers".

13:17.074 --> 13:18.362
So this your idea ?

13:22.784 --> 13:23.800
Mind if we walk ?

13:29.480 --> 13:31.325
You got dealers
selling with impunity.

13:32.070 --> 13:33.972
Addicts shooting up on the street.

13:34.623 --> 13:37.531
People down here doing outreach,
giving out needles and all.

13:38.134 --> 13:40.273
I mean, who knows about
this down at headquarters ?

13:40.285 --> 13:42.342
Command is well
aware of the situation

13:43.123 --> 13:45.795
and while there were
some initial concern

13:45.817 --> 13:48.023
but they feel the cases
that we're gonna bring in...

13:48.035 --> 13:48.579
Cases ?

13:49.016 --> 13:50.434
Yeah, prosecutions, sure.

13:50.459 --> 13:53.533
Your officers say no one's being
locked up in the free zones.

13:53.555 --> 13:55.819
My troops are only involved
in pushing the trafficking

13:55.829 --> 13:56.831
to designated areas.

13:56.913 --> 13:59.492
I mean they're completely ignorant
of the investigative aspect

13:59.501 --> 14:00.940
that's run out of C.I.D. downtown.

14:00.962 --> 14:01.530
Yeah ?

14:01.862 --> 14:03.067
Who's the lead detective ?

14:04.178 --> 14:04.900
Look...

14:06.723 --> 14:08.188
I already said more than I should.

14:08.802 --> 14:11.557
Bottom line is you start
throwing calls around right now

14:12.526 --> 14:14.619
they gonna shit blue
thinking there's a leak.

14:14.880 --> 14:16.452
They gonna come up
on the case early

14:16.464 --> 14:18.763
and we're not gonna get all
we can out of the good work

14:18.774 --> 14:19.507
we did down here.

14:19.578 --> 14:22.191
You're telling me all this
is an enforcement strategy.

14:23.752 --> 14:25.490
What the hell else could it be ?

14:26.668 --> 14:29.424
I mean, you think we'd actually
let this happen otherwise ?

14:29.931 --> 14:31.032
Come on, Banisky.

14:31.563 --> 14:33.302
I mean, look, look at this mess.

14:34.980 --> 14:36.635
Any other reporter gets on it...

14:38.530 --> 14:41.178
I give it to you and you
run with it right then.

14:41.781 --> 14:42.502
Absolutely.

14:44.156 --> 14:44.759
A week.

14:44.984 --> 14:47.019
But then I gotta run
something no matter what.

14:48.372 --> 14:49.720
<i>Purple Rain, Purple Rain.</i>

14:49.731 --> 14:50.512
It's understood.

14:54.484 --> 14:56.281
So, Brother, what
brought you back ?

14:57.333 --> 14:59.952
It disturbs me to leave
business unfinished.

15:01.136 --> 15:03.736
Heard you was shot before
you even got started down here.

15:04.528 --> 15:05.840
Not like you to get played.

15:06.242 --> 15:07.602
Betrayed, you mean.

15:08.335 --> 15:10.061
I am looking for the man they sent.

15:10.708 --> 15:13.380
From his accent he's homegrown,
raised on the street.

15:14.077 --> 15:16.868
Skilled, intelligent.
Late 20s, dark

15:17.577 --> 15:20.734
but with a scar
across his face like so.

15:22.653 --> 15:23.835
You down with this nigger ?

15:24.273 --> 15:24.876
I know him.

15:25.479 --> 15:26.366
Not to speak to

15:27.512 --> 15:29.202
but you can't be
anywhere near the game

15:29.226 --> 15:30.563
and not know
the motherfucker.

15:31.538 --> 15:32.720
He with Barksdale ?

15:33.548 --> 15:34.422
He with himself.

15:35.522 --> 15:37.874
'Cept for when he runnin'
with a young boy or two...

15:40.239 --> 15:42.083
10 months to the primary,
and you right now

15:42.095 --> 15:43.177
should be all about money.

15:43.189 --> 15:45.470
I know, I know,
dialing for dollars.

15:45.483 --> 15:48.367
You start this week and you don't
stop until you hit your numbers.

15:48.674 --> 15:50.731
We're gonna need a million
just for television.

15:50.755 --> 15:52.174
You really think this is doable ?

15:52.428 --> 15:54.473
The odds aren't great, but yeah...

15:55.017 --> 15:56.116
I think it can be done.

15:56.554 --> 15:59.272
As long as the thousand things
that can go wrong don't go wrong.

15:59.319 --> 16:00.337
Even for a white guy ?

16:01.129 --> 16:02.074
Even for a white guy.

16:02.560 --> 16:03.948
Speaking of which

16:04.422 --> 16:07.667
I notice a certain
monochromatic effect here.

16:08.288 --> 16:10.734
One thing we're gonna
need is black faces

16:11.362 --> 16:13.555
and we're gonna need them
in prominent positions.

16:13.697 --> 16:14.228
You're right.

16:14.571 --> 16:17.196
We've gotta start thinking about
endorsements by black leaders.

16:17.207 --> 16:19.962
Ministers, community people,
elected officials.

16:20.460 --> 16:21.766
Here comes the hard part:

16:22.085 --> 16:25.170
Splitting the black vote is the
only way to make the math work.

16:25.822 --> 16:27.724
So Tony Gray's gotta
get in the race

16:27.736 --> 16:30.632
he's gotta stay in the race and
he's gotta stay viable in the race.

16:30.739 --> 16:32.431
Guy's kind of a lightweight,
ain't he ?

16:32.442 --> 16:33.789
He's a good guy, all in all.

16:33.849 --> 16:35.623
Great, he's a good guy

16:36.024 --> 16:38.306
but we need him to siphon
votes from Royce.

16:38.447 --> 16:39.004
I dunno.

16:39.867 --> 16:40.860
This thing with Tony...

16:41.616 --> 16:43.128
it's not personal, Tommy.

16:43.495 --> 16:44.488
It's politics.

16:45.800 --> 16:46.829
Live with it or lose.

16:51.072 --> 16:51.781
<i>Hey, yo.</i>

16:51.842 --> 16:54.189
<i>That boy with the sharp nose,
he gonna, you know...</i>

16:54.200 --> 16:55.228
<i>he going to the Apollo.</i>

16:55.240 --> 16:56.045
<i>The Apollo ?</i>

16:56.150 --> 16:57.924
<i>Yeah, he gonna need two tickets.</i>

16:58.113 --> 17:00.053
<i>Damn, Tweety Bird
workin' that shit.</i>

17:00.064 --> 17:02.972
<i>Motherfucker, how many times
I gotta tell you not to use no names ?</i>

17:02.985 --> 17:05.017
<i>Oh yeah, right.
So I holler at you ?</i>

17:05.313 --> 17:06.318
<i>Yeah, a-ight.</i>

17:08.103 --> 17:09.486
Apollo, like the theater ?

17:09.521 --> 17:10.881
Like 125th Street.

17:11.094 --> 17:13.565
125 grams, one eighth of a kilo.

17:13.589 --> 17:15.133
Two tickets means twice that.

17:15.167 --> 17:17.023
Only new code so
far is Hamsterdam.

17:17.224 --> 17:18.112
Hamsterdam ?

17:18.219 --> 17:21.090
We're thinkin' it might have
something to do with the stash house.

17:21.730 --> 17:24.377
Well, I'm gonna hook up with Kima,
cash the Tweety Bird meet.

17:26.368 --> 17:28.048
You're happy with
what we're getting ?

17:28.592 --> 17:31.264
Another week of calls like this
and we'll have their network

17:31.299 --> 17:33.546
fleshed out and plenty
more phones to go up on.

17:35.551 --> 17:37.146
I need a moment with the detectives.

17:38.566 --> 17:39.039
Sure.

17:43.542 --> 17:45.399
I.I.D. picked up Prez's shooting.

17:45.505 --> 17:46.386
It's to be expected.

17:46.469 --> 17:49.011
The racial thing alone is tense
enough that they gotta react.

17:49.022 --> 17:50.690
No luck at all to that boy, huh ?

17:52.498 --> 17:53.929
For the supervisor's report

17:54.922 --> 17:56.228
I need to ask if either of you

17:56.240 --> 17:58.746
had any indication that Prez
harbored racial prejudices.

17:59.444 --> 18:02.045
Well, he harbored
some weird shit, no doubt.

18:02.340 --> 18:03.665
But I never got a racial vibe.

18:03.937 --> 18:05.438
Lieutenant, you seriously askin' ?

18:13.543 --> 18:14.524
Not to start no shit

18:14.583 --> 18:16.712
but you think Waggoner
gets shot if he's white ?

18:16.923 --> 18:19.336
Description called
for a number one male.

18:19.548 --> 18:20.495
I'm just sayin'.

18:23.698 --> 18:27.399
The good lord set sunday
mornin' aside for church-goin'.

18:27.777 --> 18:30.633
Even kenny bird and peanut,
when they was warring,

18:30.645 --> 18:32.725
had the good sense
to respect the truce.

18:33.730 --> 18:35.457
You know them
Barksdales sent a hat ?

18:37.454 --> 18:38.424
A church crown ?

18:39.177 --> 18:41.754
Walked up, rang the bell,
and set it down on her porch.

18:42.132 --> 18:43.148
'Cause they shamed.

18:46.033 --> 18:47.547
Is Miss Josephine mendin' ?

18:47.559 --> 18:49.551
She bruised up still,
but she a-ight though.

18:50.722 --> 18:51.525
But you ain't.

18:52.495 --> 18:53.934
Not until I settle this for good.

